record.text: Charlie is retiring from federal politics.  His northern Ont riding has increased to something that is not manageable when you're a politician who is in touch with his constituents.  He will be a HUGE loss to the NDP.  He should be the leader of the party.  Canada needs @charlieangus104.bsky.social

Perhaps the fed NDP will realize the loss in light of seat prospects under Jagmeet. Maybe the prov NDP could have taken a few lessons from Charlie and won even more seats to avoid a Ford majority.  Maybe I'm grasping at straws but I  think both the federal and Ontario NDP should see  that this guy

belongs in the political arena and be doing everything they can to ensure he doesn't leave. Just MHO.
 @ndp.ca @theondy.bsky.social #ONNDP #FightingForYou #Canada  #TeamCanada #Ontario @maritstilesndp.bsky.social

record.content:
Hello! In this post I'll be sharing my process for creating this piece:
![Elf with long braids and a veil looking at the camera](https://pioppino.us-west.host.bsky.network/xrpc/com.atproto.sync.getBlob?did=did%3Aplc%3A7qitycu5fq3ijt6vkprpfhfo&cid=bafkreifakp2i4wu6nv6lk7ihdngau2kdoivlpwpwnfre25rejvvffmf4ta)

The main brush I use is the default Medibang Paint Pro marker brush. I'll sometimes use the airbrush or a texture brush for some effects at the end, like certain lighting or backgrounds.

![Previous image without colors](https://pioppino.us-west.host.bsky.network/xrpc/com.atproto.sync.getBlob?did=did%3Aplc%3A7qitycu5fq3ijt6vkprpfhfo&cid=bafkreihbwxkxpwvldya3crlc6oilmzb2yhg25s6o5nsdrtvevvzxpcfcre)
I don't start with a typical sketch. Sometimes, I'll draw the silhouette of the character to trace over, but with this piece I went straight into the lines. I like to start drawing very small and then resize it later. Some of the lines are thick and pixelated because of this.

![Previous image with only the skin and some of the hair colored in](https://pioppino.us-west.host.bsky.network/xrpc/com.atproto.sync.getBlob?did=did%3Aplc%3A7qitycu5fq3ijt6vkprpfhfo&cid=bafkreidab6ak7m2mzyytsigmhsrgpxtzoynzlwii3gfjsjtkoz7hhciyge)
When I color, I first fill in the lines with one base color so that I can use "alpha lock" to keep my colors clean. I do rendering and coloring at the same time on one layer. The skin is always first, because that's what needs the most detail. This way, I can be as messy as I want without worrying about keeping the rest of my rendering intact. Because this piece is mostly monochrome, I saved the red accents for last. Normally, I would also add the lipstick at this stage. After the skin, I do the hair, then the clothing, and finish with metallic parts like jewelry.

The image doesn't have all the colors applied so that I can show how I finish rendering one color before I move onto the next.
record.title: My Art Process

record.content:
Hello! In this post I'll be sharing my process for creating this piece:
![Elf with long braids and a veil looking at the camera](https://pioppino.us-west.host.bsky.network/xrpc/com.atproto.sync.getBlob?did=did%3Aplc%3A7qitycu5fq3ijt6vkprpfhfo&cid=bafkreifakp2i4wu6nv6lk7ihdngau2kdoivlpwpwnfre25rejvvffmf4ta)

The main brush I use is the default Medibang Paint Pro marker brush. I'll sometimes use the airbrush or a texture brush for some effects at the end, like certain lighting or backgrounds.

![Previous image without colors](https://pioppino.us-west.host.bsky.network/xrpc/com.atproto.sync.getBlob?did=did%3Aplc%3A7qitycu5fq3ijt6vkprpfhfo&cid=bafkreihbwxkxpwvldya3crlc6oilmzb2yhg25s6o5nsdrtvevvzxpcfcre)
I don't start with a typical sketch. Sometimes, I'll draw the silhouette of the character to trace over, but with this piece I went straight into the lines. I like to start drawing very small and then resize it later. Some of the lines are thick and pixelated because of this.

![Previous image with only the skin and some of the hair colored in](https://pioppino.us-west.host.bsky.network/xrpc/com.atproto.sync.getBlob?did=did%3Aplc%3A7qitycu5fq3ijt6vkprpfhfo&cid=bafkreidab6ak7m2mzyytsigmhsrgpxtzoynzlwii3gfjsjtkoz7hhciyge)
When I color, I first fill in the lines with one base color so that I can use "alpha lock" to keep my colors clean. I do rendering and coloring at the same time on one layer. The skin is always first, because that's what needs the most detail. This way, I can be as messy as I want without worrying about keeping the rest of my rendering intact. Because this piece is mostly monochrome, I saved the red accents for last. Normally, I would also add the lipstick at this stage. After the skin, I do the hair, then the clothing, and finish with metallic parts like jewelry.

The image doesn't have all the colors applied so that I can show how I finish rendering one color before I move onto the next.

You'll notice that the lines changed between the colored and finished versions. This is because I like to make the lineart layer a clipping mask, so that it's clipped to the color layer. I don't always do this, because sometimes it makes the piece look strange. I also make the lines a dark blue instead of black to match the colors of the drawing.

record.body:
『There Is No Antimemetics Division』は、作家qntm（本名：サム・ヒューズ）によって執筆された作品で、SCP財団の世界観を舞台にしています。この物語は、自己検閲的な性質を持ち、拡散や認識を困難にする「アンタイミーム（antimeme）」と呼ばれる概念や存在に焦点を当てています。これらのアンタイミームは、人々の記憶や情報を消去し、自らの存在を隠蔽する特性を持ちます。そのため、SCP財団内でも「アンタイミーム部門」の存在や活動は忘れ去られがちであり、部門の長であるマリオン・ウィーラーでさえ、他の職員から認識されないことがあります。物語は、ウィーラーや彼女の同僚たちが、この認識不可能な脅威と対峙し、人類を守るために奮闘する様子を描いています。彼らは、記憶を強化する薬剤「ネスティクス（mnestics）」や、逆に記憶を消去する「アムネスティクス（amnestics）」を駆使し、アンタイミームに立ち向かいます。物語は、現実と非現実の境界を曖昧にし、読者にパラノイア的な緊張感を与える構成となっています。全体を通じて、人間の記憶や認識の脆弱性、そして未知の脅威に対する人類の闘争をテーマとしています。

---
情報源

以下は、前回の要約を作成する際に参考にした情報源のリストです。

1. **Grimdark Magazine**によるレビュー記事
   - このレビューでは、物語の概要や主要キャラクターであるマリオン・ウィーラーの描写、アンタイミームの概念などが詳述されています。 citeturn0search3

2. **newbookrecommendation.com**の要約記事
   - アンタイミームの定義や物語の構成、テーマ、登場人物など、作品全体の詳細な要約が提供されています。 citeturn0search1

3. **The Quill to Live**のレビュー記事
   - 作品の構造、テーマ、キャラクター描写などに焦点を当て、物語の深層に迫るレビューが掲載されています。 citeturn0search8

4. **Lakeside School Tatler**の書評
   - 作品のテーマ、キャラクター、物語の進行など、多角的な視点からの分析が行われています。 citeturn0search7

5. **Xed's Blog**のレビュー記事
   - アンタイミームの概念や物語のスタイル、構成など、作品の独自性に焦点を当てたレビューが掲載されています。 citeturn0search5

これらの情報源を基に、前回の要約を作成いたしました。

record.reviewText: A classic, though somewhat dated and the pacing is a bit odd. Still, nothing really bad to say about it.
A great take on the Werewolves of Ossory, adapted for family audiences with a historical element and backdrop. I like the fantastical aspect. It made me cry a few times, honestly.

It has the essence of the original film (being a sequel to An American Werewolf in London with a sixteen-year gap) but basically nothing else. Where are the practical effects? the CGI looks quite bad even for the time. Alex didn't need to die between the films, it felt unnecessary.
